defaultAre current safety measures at Level Crossings adequate?  How should they be improved?default2.1.1 
defaultThe regulations presently in place for signalled level crossings of various specified types is adequate.  The position could be improved by a review to ensure all crossings are in fact signalled 
defaultin accordance with the regulations
default and that 
defaultthe required 
defaultelec
defaulttrical or mechanical locking is in place.
default&#xa0;
default2.1.2 Examples exist, notably illustrated by the Moreton on Lugg
default accident where adequate protection was not in place.  This is a key issue and our concern is the culture that is now developing in the railway industry.
default&#xa0;
default2.1.3 
defaultFollowing the Clapham Accident
default on 12
defaultth
default Dec 1988 Antony Hidden QC made recommendations that were
default accepted by the industry.  One of the most important was No 50 which stated:  
default“BR
default shall ensure that the organisational framework exists to prevent commercial considerations of a business led railway from compromising safety”
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is our view that commercia
defaultl considerations surrounding the installation of Approach Locking, a standard procedure, prevented
default that safe system being applied 
defaultd
defaultespite knowledge within the industry that it was missing.
